Sentencas: Highly porous Pt/Al thin film electrodes on yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolytes were prepared by dealloying of co-sputtered Pt/Al films.
Titulo: Dealloying of platinum-aluminum thin films: Electrode performance

Sentencas: The oxygen reduction capability of the resulting electrodes was analyzed in a solid oxide fuel cell setup at elevated temperatures.
Titulo: Dealloying of platinum-aluminum thin films: Electrode performance

Sentencas: During initial heating to 523 K, exceptionally high performances compared to conventional Pt thin film electrodes were measured.
Titulo: Dealloying of platinum-aluminum thin films: Electrode performance

Sentencas: This results from the high internal surface area and large three phase boundary length obtained by the dealloying process.
Titulo: Dealloying of platinum-aluminum thin films: Electrode performance

Sentencas: Exposure to elevated temperatures of 673 or 873 K gave rise to degradation of the electrode performance, which was primarily attributed to the oxidation of remaining Al in the thin films.
Titulo: Dealloying of platinum-aluminum thin films: Electrode performance
